    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Forests under supervision of a national government.These are tracts intended for purposes of conservation of water, plant and wildlife, and public recreation. In the United States, national forests are administered  by the Forest Service in the Department of Agriculture.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
